## Motion Gaps — The Most Common Mistake

A **motion gap** is a UI change that happens without any transition. Elements snap in and out. Panels appear instantly. Loading states cut directly to content. These are the most common and most impactful motion problems in any codebase.

**Always audit for motion gaps.** Search for:

```tsx
// Conditional renders that snap
{isOpen && <Modal />}           // → needs AnimatePresence
{mode === 'a' && <PanelA />}    // → needs AnimatePresence
{isLoading ? <Spinner /> : <Content />}  // → needs AnimatePresence

// Height/size changes without transition
style={{ height: isExpanded ? 200 : 0 }}  // → needs CSS transition or layout animation
```

**Where motion gaps hide:**
- Settings and inspector panels with mode switches
- Conditional form fields that appear/disappear
- Tab content areas
- Expandable/collapsible sections
- Toast and notification systems
- Loading → content transitions
- Error state appearances

**The fix pattern** (Framer Motion):
```tsx
import { AnimatePresence, motion } from 'framer-motion'

<AnimatePresence>
  {isOpen && (
    <motion.div
      initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 8, filter: 'blur(4px)' }}
      animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0, filter: 'blur(0px)' }}
      exit={{ opacity: 0, y: 4, filter: 'blur(2px)' }}
      transition={{ type: 'spring', duration: 0.45, bounce: 0 }}
    >
      {children}
    </motion.div>
  )}
</AnimatePresence>
```

---

## Enter & Exit Recipes

### Standard Enter (Jakub — use for most UI)
```tsx
initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 8, filter: 'blur(4px)' }}
animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0, filter: 'blur(0px)' }}
transition={{ type: 'spring', duration: 0.45, bounce: 0 }}
```

### Standard Exit (subtler than enter)
```tsx
exit={{ opacity: 0, y: 4, filter: 'blur(2px)' }}
// Note: smaller y value, smaller blur — exits should be quieter
```

### Dropdown / Popover (Emil — originates from trigger)
```tsx
initial={{ opacity: 0, scale: 0.95 }}
animate={{ opacity: 1, scale: 1 }}
transition={{ duration: 0.15, ease: 'easeOut' }}
// Set transform-origin to where the trigger is (top, bottom-left, etc.)
style={{ transformOrigin: 'top left' }}
```

### Press Feedback (Jakub/Jhey — tactile)
```tsx
// Tailwind
className="active:scale-95 transition-transform duration-100"

// Or Framer Motion
whileTap={{ scale: 0.95 }}
```

### Hover State (Jakub — never instant)
```tsx
// Minimum 150ms — instant feels cheap
className="transition-colors duration-150 hover:bg-accent"
```

### List Stagger (Jhey — first 4–6 items only)
```tsx
// Parent
<motion.ul>
  {items.slice(0, 6).map((item, i) => (
    <motion.li
      key={item.id}
      initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 8 }}
      animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
      transition={{ delay: i * 0.05, duration: 0.3 }}
    />
  ))}
</motion.ul>
// Items beyond index 5 appear without stagger
```

### Icon Swap Animation (Jakub)
```tsx
// Use AnimatePresence with mode="wait" for icon swaps
<AnimatePresence mode="wait">
  {isPlaying ? (
    <motion.div key="pause"
      initial={{ opacity: 0, scale: 0.8, filter: 'blur(4px)' }}
      animate={{ opacity: 1, scale: 1, filter: 'blur(0px)' }}
      exit={{ opacity: 0, scale: 0.8, filter: 'blur(4px)' }}
      transition={{ duration: 0.15 }}
    >
      <PauseIcon />
    </motion.div>
  ) : (
    <motion.div key="play" /* same animation */ >
      <PlayIcon />
    </motion.div>
  )}
</AnimatePresence>
```

