## Duration Guidelines

Duration is **context-dependent**. Do not apply a single rule everywhere.

| Interaction Type | Duration | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Micro-interactions (press, hover) | 100–150ms | Faster = more responsive |
| Dropdowns, tooltips | 150–200ms | Emil territory |
| Panels, drawers, modals | 250–350ms | Jakub territory |
| Page transitions | 300–500ms | Depends on distance |
| Celebration/delight | Whatever serves it | Jhey territory |
| Loading → content | 300–450ms | Don't rush this one |

**Do not flag durations over 300ms as errors without checking project type first.** A 500ms spring on a consumer app modal is correct. The same duration on a productivity tool button is wrong.

