## Performance

**GPU-composited properties are always safe:** `transform`, `opacity`, `filter`

**Promote elements to their own layer** when animating complex components:
```css
/* Only use when actually needed — unnecessary promotion wastes memory */
.will-animate {
  will-change: transform, opacity;
}
/* Remove after animation completes */
```

**Framer Motion performance tips:**
- Use `layout` animations sparingly — they measure the DOM and can be expensive
- `AnimatePresence` with many items simultaneously can be costly — stagger or limit
- Prefer CSS transitions over JS animations for simple hover/focus states
- `transform` in Framer Motion is hardware accelerated by default

**Never:**
- Animate `box-shadow` on low-end devices (expensive repaint) — use `opacity` on a pseudo-element instead
- Run `requestAnimationFrame` loops that touch layout properties
- Animate more than ~20 elements simultaneously without virtualization

