## Framer Motion: Essential Patterns

```tsx
// Layout animation (size/position changes)
<motion.div layout />

// Shared layout between components
<motion.div layoutId="shared-element" />

// Animate presence (mount/unmount)
<AnimatePresence mode="wait">
  {condition && <motion.div key="unique-key" />}
</AnimatePresence>

// Gesture animations
<motion.button
  whileHover={{ scale: 1.02 }}
  whileTap={{ scale: 0.98 }}
/>

// Variants (reusable animation sets)
const variants = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0, y: 8 },
  visible: { opacity: 1, y: 0 },
  exit: { opacity: 0, y: 4 }
}
<motion.div variants={variants} initial="hidden" animate="visible" exit="exit" />

// Stagger children
const containerVariants = {
  visible: {
    transition: { staggerChildren: 0.05 }
  }
}
```

---

## Quick Audit Checklist

Before shipping any animated component, run through these:

- [ ] Is every conditional render wrapped in `AnimatePresence`?
- [ ] Do exits exist and are they subtler than enters?
- [ ] Is `useReducedMotion()` checked and respected?
- [ ] Are only `transform` and `opacity` (and `filter`) being animated?
- [ ] Is `transform-origin` set correctly on dropdowns/popovers?
- [ ] Are hover transitions at least 150ms?
- [ ] Is scale starting from 0.9+ not 0?
- [ ] Is the duration appropriate for the project type?
- [ ] Are list stagger animations limited to first 4–6 items?
- [ ] Do springs use `bounce: 0` in professional contexts?
